D. Acquisition Strategy
The IAC acquisition strategy focuses on maximal efficiency and mission responsiveness by leveraging the existing IACMAC. This multi-award contract vehicle allows for
rapid, competitive awards to a pre-qualified base of highly specialized industry partners. Core program funding is used to maintain the essential program management
infrastructure that provides oversight and drives the strategic reuse of data.
This infrastructure enables a maximum cost-sharing model, in part funded through customer reimbursements for direct task-order costs as approved by the IAC
Reimbursable Review Board (IRRB) and in strict accordance with OSW and General Counsel guidance. This dual-funding model ensures that core appropriated funds
are prioritized to build a resilient, shared capability that benefits all DoW stakeholders.




