Title: Advanced Microsystems Manufacturing Technologies Studies and Concepts                                                          2.970             -               -
Description: The Advanced Microsystems Manufacturing Technologies Studies and Concepts examined the infrastructure
needed to bring sustainability to advanced microsystems. Studies examined technologies that could reduce the cost and time-to-
market footprint of microsystems manufacturing as well as foundational ecosystem enhancements that could provide far-reaching
impact. This program also examined ways to take advantage of commercial scaling while building in superior capabilities for
defense systems through design and integration. These studies led to the development of new programs in these areas.

