A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Organic Precision Fires (OPF) program supports the Commandant of the Marine Corps' (CMC) Force Design initiative, and is in direct response to the Secretary of
War's mandate for a more lethal and distributed Joint Force. This program equips multiple levels of command within the Fleet Marine Force with an organic, loitering,
and precise "over-the-horizon" strike capability, fundamentally changing the tactical equation at all levels from the squad to the battalion.

By placing this capability directly into the hands of our infantry and reconnaissance Marines, OPF empowers them to engage the enemy immediately upon detection,
well beyond the range of their direct-fire weapons. This increases the lethality while simultaneously enhancing the survivability by minimizing exposure to enemy fire.

Extensive war-gaming, simulation, and real-world operational experience have validated that OPF is not merely an incremental improvement; it is a transformational
leap in combat effectiveness. It provides the small-unit leader with the tools to create dilemmas for our adversaries, hold key maritime terrain, and thrive in complex,
distributed environments where traditional fire support may be unavailable or too slow to respond. This program is essential to building the agile, highly lethal force
required to win in the contested battlefields of the future.

