Title: Logic Understanding for Complex Information Dissemination (LUCID)                                                                  -        9.221        23.673
Description: The Logic Understanding for Complex Information Dissemination (LUCID) program will create artificial intelligence
(AI) architectures that demonstrate that proofs encode software system knowledge to enable users to understand and adapt
systems in the field without needing to be experts in software architecture or formal logic. At present, system operators rely
on static, often difficult to navigate documentation, checklists, and training materials to understand their systems. Opaque/
inaccessible system behaviors and limited access to system architecture information can inhibit adaptation or problem solving
in the field. LUCID's insight is that formal proofs encode software system knowledge in a compact symbolic form, often beyond
what the specifications or requirements detail. This information can be used to problem-solve within the known operating envelope
and to identify corner and edge cases that lead to potential new operating points outside the currently accepted envelope. LUCID
will develop AI reasoning architectures that address semantic gaps, temporal reasoning, and compositional reasoning at scale to
make proofs a trusted source of system information and adaptation/problem-solving advice. If successful, LUCID technology will
enable warfighters to more effectively use software systems during high-stakes scenarios.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Begin the proof-of-concept to demonstrate that proofs encode software system knowledge to enhance system understanding
and adaptation.
- Initiate development of test scenarios and proof artifacts.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Demonstrate that proof explicitly encodes key semantic information that can be mapped to the operational context to enhance
the operator's insight.
- Develop AI architectures that enable users to enhance system understanding.

