Title: Cyber Physical systems Executing in Real time (CyPhER) Forge                                                                             -          13.820        30.410
Description: Cyber Physical systems Executing in Real time (CyPhER) Forge will revolutionize and accelerate defense Test &
Evaluation (T&E) by breaking the direct link between physical system complexity and test duration. This program seeks to reduce
required test points by an order of magnitude for developmental systems through two core innovations: 1) a real-time digital twin
incorporating multi-physics-informed surrogate modeling, uncertainty quantification, and continuous data assimilation, and 2) an
Artificial Intelligence (AI) test agent that applies the digital twin to identify novel, knowledge-maximizing maneuvers, and executes
maneuvers with machine precision autonomy while providing statistical safety guarantees. This integrated CyPhER will include
demonstration of an accelerated flight sciences test campaign using an experimental aircraft as the primary validation platform.

