Title: Dynamic Optimization for Defense of Ground bases with Electromagnetic warfare (DODGEball)                                           25.210                 -              -
Description: The Dynamic Optimization for Defense of Ground bases with Electromagnetic warfare (DODGEball) program will
develop algorithms for optimization of non-kinetic countermeasures for efficient and effective resource management in extended
campaign warfare. DODGEball will optimize heterogeneous applications of electromagnetic warfare for the defense of surface
forces and infrastructure for long duration campaigns. Technology developed under this program will transition to the Services.

Beginning in FY 2026, this program will be funded in PE 0603467E, Project DAT-02.

Title: Ouija                                                                                                                                  11.833              -                 -
Description: The Ouija program quantified the High Frequency (HF) noise environment in space and improved the
characterization of the ionosphere in support of warfighter capabilities. Ouija successfully created ionospheric measurements of
unprecedented granularity using ground equipment and satellites in very low earth orbit (VLEO) to improve ionospheric models
and better predict long-range HF propagation. Ouija technology improved performance and characterization of radars and
communication systems operating in the HF band. Technology developed under this program transitioned to the Services.

