Title: BioFuse                                                                                                                                -        6.250        33.606
Description: The BioFuse program will create disruptive biotechnologies to economically process minerals and metals without the
hazardous chemical steps traditionally required. This approach aims to reduce the nation's heavy reliance on foreign entities for
minerals and metals processing and enable the U.S. to domestically produce key components required for U.S. national security
and energy independence. By leveraging advances in synthetic biology, artificial intelligence, and machine learning, this effort will
develop new, more efficient, and economically competitive domestic mineral and metal processing capabilities. These innovations
will strengthen and reshore U.S. supply chains while providing strategic advantage for production of next generation technologies.

FY 2026 Plans:

