Title: Fleetwood                                                                                                                                -              -          20.000
Description: The Fleetwood program aims to enhance the DoW's capability to produce critical materials and molecules from
biomass sources, including agricultural and forestry residues. The program will explore solutions to provide the critical materials
to protect, support, and sustain warfighters in austere terrestrial conditions. This program will investigate novel catalytic materials
for the conversion of domestic and global biomass sources into critical materials and commodity molecules for DoW applications
and use. This program will leverage chemical and biological methods to provide enhanced materials that support the warfighter
and mission execution. The technologies developed will improve domestic manufacturing resiliency and reduce reliance on fragile
supply chains and foreign sources of these chemicals.

FY 2027 Plans:
- Investigate approaches for the development of chemical and biological processes and biologically derived materials to support
and sustain the warfighter in all conditions.



