Title: Biologically Based Materials and Devices Studies and Concepts                                                                            -              -          30.114
Description: The Biologically Based Materials and Devices Studies and Concepts thrust aims to enhance the DoW's capability
to conduct operations in varied conditions. The DoW operates in all domains, which creates a myriad of difficult burdens to the
warfighter and sustained operations. This thrust will develop solutions to protect, support, and sustain warfighters and operational
capabilities in austere conditions, whether terrestrial, aquatic, in the far atmosphere, or beyond. Technologies developed in this
thrust will leverage biological or bio-inspired components to provide enhanced materials and devices that support the warfighter
and mission execution. Research conducted will support biosurveillance and biosecurity with advanced detection systems,
predictive analytics, and innovative countermeasure development to identify, monitor, and mitigate biological threats, ensuring
global health security and resilience.

FY 2027 Plans:
- Initiate technology development for the integration of dynamic and responsive biological organisms or bio-inspired molecules
into composite materials.
- Investigate approaches for the development of biological processes and biologically derived materials to support and sustain the
warfighter in austere conditions.
- Explore methods that leverage and combine recent advances in biological sensors, interventions, and technologies to develop
novel platforms for threat detection and analysis, in both humans and agricultural crops.
- Investigate the ability of biological molecules and processes to perform calculations to enable highly adaptable and efficient
computational systems and sensors.
- Initiate technology development for biohybrid systems capable of enhanced threat sensing, protection, and remediation.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:

