       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $11.729 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $5.067 million for civilian personnel to optimize the workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, "Implementing the
       President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative."

       The decrease of ($52.006 million) in FY 2024 consist of -$11.8 million overestimation of SM-6 BLK 1B management services, -$23 million SM-6 Blk 1B
       EMD delay, -$37.5 million unjustified support growth, -$4.1 million due to BLK 1B strategy change, +$12.6 million Navy realignment, and +$25 million Israel
       Supplemental. The decrease of ($180 million) in FY 2025 due to BLK 1B acquisition strategy change. The decrease of ($55.371 million) in FY 2026 consists of -
       $174.9 million in rephasing realignment, +$140.2 million in cost overruns and realignment, and -$20.6 million in misc/rate adjustments.




