D. Acquisition Strategy
The acquisition approach is to rapidly prototype Key Enablers and Sonobuoy Enhancements that improve maritime supremacy by means of Engineering Change
Proposal (ECP) modifications to the AN/SSQ-36, AN/SSQ-53, AN/SSQ-62, AN/SSQ-101 and AN/SSQ-125 sonobuoys; rapid integration of Acoustic Communications
(ACOMMS) with government developed source code and waveforms into the Acoustic Operational Flight Program (AOFP) and the Tactical Open Missions System
(TOMS); and integrate KESE products into multiple ASW platforms. KESE increases the P-8A operational flexibility and effectiveness throughout the ASW kill chain,
resulting in maintaining maritime superiority against all foreign threats by enabling two-way ACOMMS between the P-8 and USN submarines and assures two-way
communication link between sonobuoys and processing platforms in all environments.




