Title: Humboldt                                                                                                                                 -           4.872             -
Description: The Humboldt program seeks to develop directed energy (DE) devices to produce disruptive effects in electronic
systems. The devices have potential for dual-use as sources to characterize the susceptibility of commercial electronics to
electromagnetic interference (EMI).

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded in PE 0602716E, Project ELT-01.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Develop a range of application-specific antennas.
- Experimentally characterize Humboldt devices integrated with antennas in relevant, simulated environments.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The FY 2027 decrease reflects program completion.
Title: Sync                                                                                                                                        -        4.824                -
Description: The Sync program is creating systems to defend against uncrewed underwater vehicles (UUVs) entering U.S.
harbors and ports. Today's counter-UUV approaches rely on complex detection and localization methods to find UUVs prior to
engagement. The Sync program looks at orthogonal approaches to solving this problem to defeat UUVs prior to detection. Sync is
investigating several different approaches to defeat UUVs, starting with modeling and simulation eventually moving to hardware in
the loop and pool testing.

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded in PE 0602716E, Project ELT-01.


