immediate and lasting protection even in austere operational settings.

Title: Preemptive Expression of Protective Alleles and Response Elements (PREPARE)                                                       0.120             -            -
Description: The Preemptive Expression of Protective Alleles and Response Elements (PREPARE) program aimed to create a
transient, near immediate prophylaxis and treatment to protect military personnel and civilians against public health and national
security threats. Currently, protection against Chemical, Biological, Radiological, and Nuclear (CBRN) threats relies on physical
barrier technology. This program included research to develop novel transient and reversible gene modulator therapies to bolster
intrinsic host defenses. Work within this program provided novel solutions that extend beyond the DoW's capabilities to respond to
re-emerging, newly emerging, or engineered threats.

