Title: Midway                                                                                                                                -        7.048         39.603
Description: The Midway program will develop and demonstrate a communication-based payload distributed onboard mobile
platforms in order to enable long range transmission and reception capabilities. The program will leverage commercially available
and modified commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) components to create a resilient, rapidly deployable, and scalable architecture
for data transport. This program culminates in a full-scale tactical demonstration that validates the critical technologies in a
representative environment and reduces technical, schedule, and cost risk for a follow-on operational system.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Initiate communications architecture and vehicle sizing studies.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Complete communications architecture and vehicle sizing studies.
- Initiate host platform fabrication and evaluation.
- Conduct payload integration and ground qualification testing.
- Demonstrate payload functionality in a representative environment.
