The FY 2027 increase reflects the shift from platform and payload design to fabrication and integration activities.
Title: Deep Thoughts                                                                                                                         -        4.128         15.800
Description: Deep Thoughts will expand access in the deep ocean domain by developing a new class of novel lightweight,
low-cost, and rapidly designed, produced and deployed deep-ocean Autonomous Undersea Vehicles (AUVs). The program
aims to harness breakthroughs in advanced materials, manufacturing, and next-generation structural and mechanical design
technologies to dramatically reduce the volume and mass of deep-ocean systems, while eliminating dependence on traditional
long-lead components. The foundational goal of Deep Thoughts is to achieve a neutrally buoyant, deep-ocean AUV without
relying on syntactic foam. Innovation in pressure-vessel design, including alternative materials, configurations, architectures, and

