Title: Trenton                                                                                                                           -        2.872              -
Description: The Trenton program is enabling the production of a wide range of structural objects and underwater repairs through
the optimization of three-dimensional concrete printing (3DCP) formulations and fabrications at depth. Trenton is developing the
first underwater 3DCP (U3DCP) formulations utilizing in-situ materials to support various marine engineering needs. Current
technologies rely on land-based techniques that require forming on land then deployment by barge or ship. Trenton is overcoming
this challenge by developing the formulations and fabrication technologies necessary for U3DCP. Technology developed under
this program will transition to the Services and commercial partners.

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded in PE 0603766E, Project NET-02.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Conduct capabilities testing for underwater printing of simple structures in laboratory settings.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The FY 2027 decrease reflects program completion.
Title: Willow                                                                                                                            -       28.627              -
Description: The Willow program is developing innovative payloads to conduct Acoustic Warfare (AW) to counter sonars using
a unique combination of acoustic hardware and waveforms provided by advanced sonar signal processing algorithms. Willow
provides a robust capability to help the Navy respond to sonar threats. This is a novel method for challenging adversary sonars.
Willow uses advanced hardware-in-the-loop simulations, Independent Verification and Validation (IV&V), and stressing at-sea
testing to create this capability. Technology developed under this program will transition to the Navy.

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded in PE 0603766E, Project NET-02.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue IV&V activities to verify performer updates to simulations, hardware and waveforms based on lessons learned.
- Conduct Final Design Review of acoustic systems and other technologies prior to at-sea demonstration.
- Conduct at-sea demonstration with prototype integrated system.

