B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025           FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: DARPAVERSE                                                                                                                                -              5.494       0.544
Description: The DARPAVERSE program will create a novel environment for the faster, iterative, development of operational
concepts and capabilities by factoring, decomposing, and recomposing models of full DIMEFIL (Diplomatic, Intelligence, Military,
Economic, Financial, Informational, and Legal) effects to deliver decision superiority. DARPAVERSE will enable warfighters to
develop an iterative understanding of goals, capabilities, and options using adaptive modeling to explore and visualize novel
capabilities and operational concepts with teams in immersive environments to reduce modeling and simulation costs and effort.
Analysts will be able to explore and compare options with real-time adaptive simulation capabilities to discover optimal choices
given current force structure, and the ability of new capabilities to improve outcomes. DARPAVERSE will overcome challenges in
modern concept and capability development using natural language specifications with an operator. Technology developed under
this program will transition to the Services.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Develop generalized and composable methods of automatic reduced order model development from existing models.
- Enable artificial intelligence aided definition and orchestration of custom multi-model environments with a single operator.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Transition DARPAVERSE technology.
