Title: Advanced C4 Systems Studies and Concepts                                                                                           -        4.071         32.001
Description: The Advanced C4 Systems Studies and Concepts will design and demonstrate advanced communications systems
and information systems technology to provide novel concepts and advanced capabilities to access challenging new environments
and overcome contested domains. Emphasis will be on concepts and approaches that increase situational awareness, command
and control, communications, information infrastructure, cyber operations, information operations, artificial intelligence, and
autonomous capabilities at the tactical edge. Technology advancements will support interoperability, security, and resilience.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Conduct multi-domain studies and assess impact to resilience.
- Characterize the range and imaging performance of existing radars using fundamental targets of various sizes and shapes.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Investigate fully homomorphic architecture for secure artificial reasoning on platforms in the field.
- Develop planning capabilities with artificial intelligence to support operational preparation.
- Conduct design study on impacts to integration with current mission planning software.
- Investigate forward-looking, machine-driven scenario development capable of identifying critical data sets for situational
awareness.
- Investigate potential to create a hybrid modeling environment where subject matters experts assess the utility and validity of
forecasted scenarios.
- Demonstrate feasibility of a potential secure and scalable mobile ad-hoc network for maritime vehicles.
- Investigate nonlinear mission architectures to generate decision advantage and optionality overmatch by imposing complexity
on the adversary.
- Formally evaluate operating system for network appliances.
- Generate a library of sensing target features and images that can be used for identification and classification.
- Conduct state-of-the-art analysis for current information systems technology and begin tradeoff studies.
- Meet with transition partners and government stakeholders to define situational awareness gaps.
