Title: Advanced Cyber Security Studies and Concepts                                                                                       -        3.149         16.114
Description: Efforts conducted under this thrust study, refine, prototype, demonstrate, and evaluate technologies for cyber
security and resilience of U.S. software systems. Security and resilience of the software in weapons, combat, and information
systems is essential for warfighters who rely on the correct functioning of this software for success on the battlefield. Thrust
emphasis is on dramatically enhancing the security and resilience of both new and legacy software systems that may be subject
to cyber attack by adversaries. Focus areas include enabling the confident creation of software systems that are secure by design
against exploits; the rapid remediation of software defects once discovered; and the cost-effective improvement of the legacy
software on which critical missions often depend. Technical approaches of interest include, but are not limited to, automated
vulnerability discovery and remediation, binary analysis, reverse engineering, formal methods, artificial intelligence (AI)-based
approaches, and other advanced software generation, analysis, and understanding technologies. Tools and prototypes are
created to explore new software security and resilience concepts, and evaluation and refinement of the concepts, tools, and
prototypes are performed in collaboration with software developers and cyber red teams. This thrust creates the new concepts


