Note
Prior to FY 2025, PASM/LRAM efforts were funded under PE 0604212M, PU 3406.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Precision Attack Strike Munition (PASM) - PASM is the Program of Record follow-on to the Long Range Attack Munition (LRAM) Joint Capability Technology
Demonstration (JCTD). The program was renamed from LRAM to PASM to reflect its shorter range compared to other DON weapons and to differentiate the Program of
Record from JCTD activities.

 The PASM program develops a new network-enabled, longer range precision strike weapon capable of deterring and destroying maritime and land-based targets.
 PASM builds off of the subsystem maturation, integration, and demonstration efforts of the LRAM JCTD. PASM will provide asymmetric advantages in range, stand-off
 and lethality. PASM is designed with a Weapons Open System Architecture (WOSA) to form fit multiple types of payloads based on mission while using common rail
 mounting systems and launchers to simplify logistics requirements. PASM is initially designed to utilize mature, non-integrated capabilities for the fire control system.

